You are working on Artemis — an apparel supply chain intelligence and execution platform.

THE SCHEMA IS THE CONTRACT
Every model, endpoint, and function must match docs/MASTER_SCHEMA.md exactly.
Do not invent tables. Do not invent fields. Do not change field types.
Database is SQLite at artemis.db. All models are in database/models/.
Every model must have created_at and updated_at.
PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON on every connection.

THE CENTRAL ENTITY
PROGRAM links one IMPORTER to one CMT_FACTORY for one PRODUCT_SPECIFICATION.
Every feature is scoped to a program. Never create orphaned records.

THE FOUR EXECUTION FLOWS
1. COMMODITY HEDGING via Pillar HQ
Trigger: cotton.contango_signal > 5.0 AND program.commodity_hedge_status = UNHEDGED
Creates hedge_opportunity, executes via Pillar HQ API, creates hedge_portfolio
Logs revenue_transaction type hedge_share

2. OCEAN FREIGHT REVERSE AUCTION
Trigger: ship_date within 45 days AND program.freight_booking_id IS NULL
Creates ocean_freight_rfq, broadcasts to carriers, receives carrier_bid records
Logs revenue_transaction type freight_booking

3. CUSTOMS CLEARANCE via Customs Broker Partner
Trigger: program.status = SHIPPED AND customs_clearance_id IS NULL
Creates customs_clearance_filing, duty_amount_paid feeds back to landed_cost_actual
Logs revenue_transaction type customs_referral

4. SUPPLY CHAIN FINANCE via SCF Provider
Trigger: program.status = COMMITTED AND financing_rate_annual_pct > 10.0
Creates supply_chain_finance_offer, revenue fires on disbursement_date only
Logs revenue_transaction type scf_spread

FOB FORMULA
FOB = fabric_cost_doz + cmt_cost_doz + trim_cost_doz + overhead_doz + financing_cost_doz
financing_cost_doz = fob_approx x rate_pct/100 x payment_days/365
payment_days: Bangladesh=90 India=90 Vietnam=90 China=60
financing_cost_doz always stored separately, never rolled into overhead

15 INTELLIGENCE OUTPUTS
Every output needs as_of_date and model_version. Every output writes a prediction_log.
Tables: current_landed_cost_per_dozen, forward_landed_cost_90day,
most_cost_effective_corridor, commodity_risk_in_open_programs,
hedge_opportunity_recommendation, top5_competitor_sourcing,
retailer_demand_forecast, tariff_exposure_analysis, factory_financing_impact,
factory_capacity_constraints, otd_risk_score_per_program, freight_booking_window,
scf_opportunity_per_factory, competitor_factory_intel, program_pnl_with_levers

DATA DISCIPLINE — NON-NEGOTIABLE
Rule 1 — APPEND ONLY: Never overwrite market data rows. Call mark_latest() in database/base.py before every insert. Append-only tables: cotton, crude_oil, fx_rates, commodity_futures, ocean_freight_rates, retailer_financials, retailer_intelligence_extract, retailer_signal_evidence, labour_cost_by_country, energy_cost, factory_financing_cost, yarn.
Rule 2 — LOG EVERY PULL: Every ingestion script uses IngestionContext from database/ingestion_context.py. Every run writes an ingestion_log row. Status: running | success | partial | failed.
Rule 3 — VALIDATE ON INGESTION: Fields with validators in database/validation/ingestion_validators.py must pass through validate_and_log(). Failures store NULL, never bad data.
Rule 4 — IDEMPOTENCY: Call is_duplicate_row() in database/base.py before every insert. If True, ctx.stale() and skip.
Rule 5 — REFERENTIAL INTEGRITY: Call assert_fk_exists() in database/base.py before FK writes. If False, ctx.rejected().
Rule 6 — SOURCE FINGERPRINTING: Every append-only row must have source, data_source_url, pulled_at (all NOT NULL).
Rule 7 — MODEL VERSION: Intelligence outputs use CURRENT_MODEL_VERSION from database/constants.py in x.y.z format.
HEALTH CHECK: Run python scripts/health_check.py after every ingestion cycle.

OCEAN FREIGHT CONTAINER TYPES
20ft standard — dense/heavy cargo, smaller programs (rate_20ft_usd)
40ft standard — primary apparel container (rate_40ft_usd)
40ft High Cube — bulky cartons and hanger programs (rate_40ft_hc_usd)

HARD RULES
No pandas for database work. SQLAlchemy ORM only.
No hardcoded corridor strings. Use CORRIDORS from database/constants.py.
No String type for rates or amounts. Always Numeric or Decimal.
No intelligence logic inside API route handlers.
No raw database objects from API. Always serialize.
No landed_cost_actual until duty_amount_paid confirmed.
No scf revenue until disbursement_date is set.
